               <interp inst="t18350615-1587" type="date" value="18350615"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18350615-1587-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1587-18350615 t18350615-1587-offence-1 t18350615-1587-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1587. <persName id="def1-1587-18350615" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1587-18350615" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1587-18350615" type="surname" value="BURFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1587-18350615" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE BURFIELD</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted<rs id="t18350615-1587-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350615-1587-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350615-1587-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18350615-cd-188" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350615-1587-offence-1 t18350615-cd-188"></join>27th of April</rs>, 10 loaves of bread, value 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and a basket; the goods of <persName id="t18350615-name-1271" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1271" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1271" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1271" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350615-1587-offence-1 t18350615-name-1271"></join>Joseph Adams</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1272" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1272" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1272" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1272" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH ADAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner was in my service. He had taken seven<lb></lb>teen loaves out on the 27th of April—seven he delivered, and ten I charge him with stealing—he had ten loaves the second time, and seven loaves the first time—he was to return at half-past twelve, to attend to his business—I never saw him till he was in custody—my wife went and found the basket at a public-house—she brought it home—I found afterwards that he was at Union-hall.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was it you gave him the bread? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; Mrs. Adams gave it him both times—it was the same day on which the last charge is made.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MRS. ADAMS</hi>. I am the prosecutor's wife. I served the prisoner with</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183506150193"></xptr>
               <p>seven loaves, and then with ten—the first seven were to be delivered in the round in which Rodda lived, and the others in the district in which Johnson and Taylor live.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he account for the first seven? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; he took seven out and then came back and had ten—the general rule is to book the bread when he has done serving all his customers—I cannot say what he had left out of <hi rend="italic"></hi> the seven or out of the ten—the basket was found at the public-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You gave the loaves to the prisoner? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I did not give him directions to distribute them in the different walks be<lb></lb>cause he knows them—I will not undertake to swear that he might not deliver these loaves, or some of them, to Rodda, Johnson, and Taylor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JOSEPH ADAMS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What was the 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> That was for what she had had the latter end of the week, and what they had that day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1273" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1273" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1273" type="surname" value="RODDA"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1273" type="given" value="LYDIA"></interp>LYDIA RODDA</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I only had one 4lb. and one 21b. loaf that day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1274" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1274" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1274" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1274" type="given" value="SUSAN"></interp>SUSAN JOHNSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I had two leaves.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">STEPHEN TAYLOR</hi>. I cannot say how many I had—I am cer<lb></lb>tain I had not less than one loaf.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I got intoxicated and left the basket at the public-house while I went to get the money. While I was gone he sent two officers to my house—I thought I would rather not be taken, and went further away—I was afterwards returning to get the money to send him, but they had me taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18350615-1587-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-1587-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-1587-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value=""></interp>NOT GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Second Jury, before Mr. Sergeant Arabin</hi>.</p>
            </div1>
